HEADWORD: Eupione
<hw>Eu"pi*one</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ very fat;
<grk>e'y^</grk> well + <?/ fat.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A limpid,
oily liquid obtained by the destructive distillation of various
vegetable and animal substances; -- specifically, an oil consisting
largely of the higher hydrocarbons of the paraffin series.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>eupion</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eupittone</ent>⟦br⟧
